<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="46" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,644]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,584,608]" pageId="7" pageNumber="46">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName box="[905,1018,583,607]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguriahana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="singularis">singularis</taxonomicName>
” which refers to the single process of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
